The paper deals with the optimization of channel training in energy harvesting communication systems, which involves the use of information theory, networking, and control systems. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) are the most likely categories. The paper also discusses the impact of training optimization on the overall system performance, which involves system-level considerations and control theory, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a likely category as well. Additionally, the paper uses simulations to evaluate the proposed solutions, which involves machine learning and data analysis, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible category. Finally, the paper proposes adaptive solutions that adjust the training period and power based on the energy profile, which involves statistical learning and optimization, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible category.
